                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.14473/2603.14473v1/x2.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:Overview of Reinforcement Learning from Community Feedback (RLCF).(1)Community feedback is collected as pairwise preference signals\nfrom naturally occurring community behavior.(2)A preference model is trained via GRPO to predict which item\nin a pair receives stronger community reception.(3)A policy model is trained via comparison-based GRPO: for each\ninput, the policy samples a group of outputs, the preference model conducts\npairwise comparisons to produce scalar rewards, and the policy is updated\naccordingly. In this work, we instantiate RLCF for scientific taste learning,\nwhere community feedback is derived from citation signals.",
